HEADWORD: Therapeutae
<hw>Ther`a*peu"tae</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <?/ (pl. <?/) an attendant, servant, physician. See
<er>Therapeutic</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld> <def>A name given
to certain ascetics said to have anciently dwelt in the neighborhood of
Alexandria. They are described in a work attributed to Philo, the
genuineness and credibility of which are now much discredited.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

